      "content": "I'm not a doctor, but I can provide some general guidance. Dropping down from 5mg to 2mg of warfarin might not be the best idea, as your body may need the higher dose to maintain the desired anticoagulant effect. A sudden change in dosage can lead to thrombotic complications, so it's best to consult your doctor before making any adjustments.",
