      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can't advise you on how to self-manage your warfarin dosage without consulting a doctor. If you're concerned about your medication, I recommend speaking with your doctor about your concerns. \n\nIf you still want to consider the lower dose, some signs that 2mg might be effective include minimal bruising, no unusual bleeding, and your doctor's approval, which would likely involve a follow-up blood test. However, these signs don't necessarily confirm the dosage is correct.",
